                     <p> 
                        <placeName key="place_107067">STOKE (North)</placeName>. Convention dated the Sunday after the feast
                  of St. Matthew the apostle, <origDate notBefore="1274-11-20" notAfter="1275-11-19">3 Ed. I</origDate>, by which <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename>, the prior</persName>,
                  and <orgName key="org_107004">convent of Wallingford</orgName> grant to farm to 
                  <persName nymRef="Bornfeld">
                           <forename>John</forename>
                        </persName> son of 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Bornfeld</surname>
                        </persName> the whole of
                  the land in the village of <placeName key="place_107067">North Stoke</placeName> which they have by reason of the custody of
                  the land and heirship of <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Croc</surname>
                        </persName> to hold until
                  the said Roger is of full age, paying annually 23s. 
                  </p>
